name: Barish Turker
artist_bio:
Barish is one of Turkey's leading djs, hosting three different weekly shows @ Dinamo 103.8 (www.dinamo.fm) which he is also in charge of music directing. He is also the resident Dj of Crobar BoraMusic HouseCast, a two time IDMA nominated house music podcast with guest DJ mixes and interviews from the world's top DJs. Always looking ahead, he tries to break boundaries with his genre defying variations, building up a dedicated crowd all around.

Barish is a dedicated music lover, and an established dj. His passion for music began with his long escapades into the world of R'n'b and Soul. While studying architectural engineering at the University of Hartford, his mad nights during the early times of Twilo made him fall in love with electronic music and its performance.  

After graduation, he moved to New York for business opportunities and that's where his dj'ing career took off.  After winning a mixing competition held by New York City’s DJ Mark Divine (Sound Factory), Barish secured himself two local weekly residencies at the Leopard Lounge and Liquids sharing the booth respectively with Mark Divine (D3) and Julio Terra (MuzakTherapy). 

After returning to his native country , Barish quickly became a resident at Turkey’s most prestigious clubs such as Crystal, Nuclub and Underground.  During this time Barish has become one of the principal member DJs of the highly regarded “Together” crew notably comprising international house talents such as Yunus Guvenen, Subsky, & Muzo B. His evergrowing ‘Wet’n’Juicee’ nights at NuClub had been a landmark for house music lovers in the past few years and his recent residencies at Club Clinic and Multidance has been making a great impact, not to mention his opening performance for François K at Istanbul’s Surmeli, an extended set at Dinamo’s Radar Live Festival.and his recent performance at Arro Dance, Bulgaria.

Barish has been DJ’ing with a pious dedication since early 2000 and his hard work is felt in his key mixing abilities and exceptional track selection. He is known by his friends as one of the most disciplined and motivated Dj in the country, nothing can tear him apart from the booth not even a broken leg! His blend of unique sounds, unprejudiced genre defying variations and rather hypnotic approach has caught the attention of IDJ magazine, which commented his set with great review in the Readers’ Mixes Section on May 2003 issue.  Barish has started to host for 34 BPM shows on the internet’s leading dance broadcast Proton Radio after his brilliant guest mixes and his sets also appeared on selected radio servers such as Mercurysessions, Musicserver.uk, Frisky, etc.

Barish has been performing around the US and eastern Europe for the last few years including 
- Miami (Proton Radio Party w/Subsky, Dinamo Party  w/ Fuchs, Joshua Collins.., Red Flag Collective & Angora Records’ Collaborative party w/ Ozgur Can, Astro&Glyde..) 
- New York (Swamy’s Sunday night party at Le Souk w/ Astro & Glyde, Loft’n’Space Party at Robots)
- Hartford (Red Flag Collective Release Party w/ Yunus)
- Bulgaria (Arro Dance, Life House & Comics Club)
- Poland (Piekarnia, Klatka & Mandragora)
- Romania (Kristal Club)
- Hungary (Dokk Club - Red Flag Collective Release Party w/ Yunus)
- Russia (live performance with Burhan Öçal at Turquality Fashion Project at Moscow’s Music House) 

Barish and Muzo B’s collaborative project, a Digweed favorite “Adequate Medication”, was first spotted at Sasha&Digweed Coloursfest ’03 radio set and released on December through Red Flag Collective, a record label he started with Yunus Güvenen, Subsky and Muzo B being responsible for label's promotion and also working as the A&R Coordinator along with Subsky.  Barish and Muzo’s other monstrous project ‘Intra-Venous’ took place on Digweed’s September ’05 Chart and got released through their digital platform.

Barish is the music director at Istanbul’s independent electronic music station Dinamo 103.8 (www.dinamo.fm).  He has three different weekly shows called Section, LOW & Wet'n'Juicee Sessions that has been shaking the airwaves since 2002 and it did not take them too long to be chosen as the most listened alternative radio station in Turkey, that also led Bpm magazine (Sept. 2005 issue) to cover the growing success in its ‘Istanbul Shakers’ article including an interview with Barish himself. 

Barish has recently become the new Crobar BoraMusic Housecast resident DJ. An IDMA nominated House Music Podcast with guest DJ mixes and interviews from the world's top DJs. Some of the previous episodes include artists such as Bob Sinclar, Martin Solveig, Fedde le Grand, Sasha, Dubfire and many more to come in 2009 with Barish serving up a weekly selection.

name: Cagri Eralp
artist_bio:
Cagri Eralp or with well known moniker CE is on the music scene for more then 15 years as a producer , dj and vocalist.

While working as a production manager and musical director on well known radio stations around Turkey and djing around the countries like England , Russia , Romania , Bulgaria and Germany, he did the vocals of many dance floor hits which are released on labels like Choo Choo , Nascent , DeepXperience Productions , Subversive Records, Flash Records
Çagri Eralp or well known moniker "CE" started his career in 1992 by Dj’ing at one of friend's birthday party. This first gig was so successful which led to weekend parties, and short after CE got an offer from local club for weekend residency.

Same year CE got his own slot on one and only radio station of region at the time, "Tempo FM". His first radio show "megamix" was on air for 3 years in the meanwhile CE promoted to be production manager of "Tempo FM".

In 1995 he continued his radio career on "Radio Star" as musical director and production manager, his show continued with sponsorship of Nokia for another 2 years.

Finaly at the end of 1996 after 5 years local radio experience and being top DJ of region he moved in to legendary dance music station "Radio Cool" as production manager. "Radio Cool" was one of the leading dance music stations at the time in Turkey and gave him opportunity to work with best DJ's and producers in Turkey. In the meantime he was Resident DJ of legendary "The Castle", and hosting around 1500 people every weekend which spread the name around the region.

In year 1999 CE moved to UK to continue his higher education. In year 2000 while he was a resident DJ of local club in London, one of his friend invited musical director of a DJ agency to listen CE's flawless groovy house set - without CE knowing it - which ended playing in hot spots around UK as well as weekend residency on Tiger Tiger.

In year 2002 he returned to Turkey, continued in Radio Cool as production manager and hosted his own radio shows "Global Rotation" and "Free Fall". Contributed Turkish pop artists by co-producing and remixing their tracks.

In year 2003 he contributed Mert Yucel's 12” "DeepXperince EP" with vocals which was released by "ChooChoo Records" in UK. Collaboration with Mert Yucel continued with another 12": “Microwave EP” which was released by Nascent Records and track named "Heavy addictive" in "Gen Up EP" which was no.9 on North American charts, released by "Mo-Do Records: of Italy, also continued his DJ career in all events of Radio Cool as well as residency in legendary "Olympos" in Antalya.

In year 2004 after more than 8000 hours broadcast on air, many successful parties he decided to move in Moscow. He never quit producing and Jing around the globe while he was working as an IT professional. Same year he appeared in Mert Yucel's 12": "Get into my groove EP" which was released by "Subversive Records" in UK.

In year 2005 while being signed artist on DeepXperience and collaborating Mert Yucel on another dance floor smasher "Mickey Bizness" which was released by DeepXperience, CE collaborated with Turkey's best DJ "Tarkan" and talented producer "Dammex" on "In a dream" which was huge success and charted by many top DJs around the globe, appeared on many compilations as well as its video aired exclusively on MTV.

Same year he also appeared in Fitalic's "Control your mind" which was released by "Plastic Park records" of Germany and 4Mal's "First sense" which appeared in "Trance Nation Presents Progressive Interpretation" in Germany. First sense had huge reaction from Russian and Spanish dance music scene as well as all around the globe.

In year 2006 CE was back in scene on another DeepXperience release, phat, tribal dance floor killer "One Two" with talented Greek producer "Alex Celler" from UK and appeared in Fitalic's "Atomic Atmosphere" album which was released by "Tribal Visions" in CZ.

In year 2007 CE collaborated Mert Yucel in "Need the House" which got support from big names like Saeed Younan and Tony Thomas and re-release of "Mickey Bizness" with remixes Alex Celler and Vancouver's Tyler Lewis.

In year 2008 CE contributed "Pilot Presents Sergey Tkachev" in "Exciter" (4Mal Feat. Cagri Eralp Remix) which was released by "Flash Records".

In year 2009 CE contributed Sergey Tkachev's "Like That" which was huge success in Kazantip.

In year 2010 his legendary vocal in "Living in a dream" was back in scene with remixes by Dr. K & Nii vs. SHIHA,Nicolas Coronel & Juan Pablo Graziano, Darioef, Bojan Janjic a.k.a. DJ Zuba & Elvir Bandic and Gui Sheffer.

As he describes himself as an "underground" DJ and producer, his DJing style is unpredictable, depending on venue and crowd: house music blended with techy loops and deep grooves as well as intelligent electro. He also shared booth with many well known DJs such as Steve Lawler, Sander Kleinenberg, Barry Gilbey, Dj Chus, Jamie Anderson to name a few...

name: Christopher Çolak
artist_bio:
Christopher Çolak aka Chriak or Christereo is an Istanbul based visual communication & type designer, music writer, radio programmer and DJ. He has contributed more than 300 articles and interviews, including top notch producers, bands and artists from all around the world.Christopher Çolak is the founder of the bilingual online music publication Halfstereo. He is also a freelance writer at Babylon Magazine and he writes weekly feeds at Le Cool's Istanbul edition.

His radio show 'fraktal' is live every Tueasday night around 20:00-21:00 hours(local) at Dinamo 103.8 FM Istanbul since 2005, promising the best and unreleased releases of various electronic dance music spectrum.

'Login' is the alternate and is broadcasted live every Saturday night between 23:00-00:00 hours(local) this time dealing with the more experimental side and upper cases of electronic music since late 2002. From old school jungle to dubstep, from post folk to noise is where you may lead during the show.

From the beginning to the end, he has been a music writer for the famous Basatap Magazine, TimeOut Istanbul Mag and IKSV's (Istanbul Foundation for Culture and Arts) Istanbuldostlari.org projects. He was the editor of one of the best and first clubbing & electronic portals in Turkey, legendary Clubintro.

Now he resides under his own HalfStereo and continues his radio programs and occasionaly DJs on some selected events. His sets are never linear, going amongst disco, minimal tech house to deep house, nujazz and even MDR style techno and some surprizes! His sound is more likely the mixture of Clone/Rotterdam sound blended with the Berliner minimal and techy edge. But he can also play a well defined nujazz or nudisco set as well. No matter what genre it is, good music and good groove is the key.

He has played with Apparat, Jeff Samuel, Andy Vaz, Martin Eyerer, Michal Ho and most lately Vector Lovers at various locations which were and are the hot spots of Istanbul night life.

name: AudioKnob
artist_bio:
International performer Dj Beyza & accomplished musician Cuneyt Karayalcin combine their passion and power for only one reason : producing and remixing music – a distinct repertoire of tracks filled with emotion, harmony, rhythm and melody. Take punchy beats, add walking basslines, driving grooves, some “less-is-more” synth parts and mix it up with mellow guitars, altered bass guitar riffs, and smooth keys – there you have the sound of AudioKnob. The production/dj duo are inspired from an interesting cross-section of styles including multiple musical worlds such as, Minimal Techno and House, elements of Rock and Funk, and even the oriental character and diversity of Turkish Music. As a live act, the duo incorporate a cool and energetic mix of underlying dance grooves with live electronics,..Members:

Dj Beyza

Since 1997, Beyza has been at the forefront of the electronic music scene in her hometown of Istanbul, Turkey. Early in her career, she was chosen to play at the largest open air club of Europe - 2019. Following these early gigs, Beyza quickly ascended to the height of Istanbul's underground scene and beyond. Her trips as a professional DJ have not only taken her to venues all over Turkey, but help her stretch as far as France, Cyprus, Germany, Austria, Romania, Georgia, Bulgaria, Ukrania, Polland and the US. From small intimate clubs and larger beach parties to massive New Year's Events, Beyza has only begun to accomplish the vision she has set forth. Her abilities have grown beyond the DJ booth, and have spread to the production studio. Now, thanks to her endless search for musical discovery, DJ Beyza has forged an international reputation and attracted large crowds whereever she plays.

Cuneyt Karayalcin

Cuneyt Karayalcin started his professional music career in 1997 by joining to the pioneers of Turkish Metal "Cenotaph" and "Omnious Grief". By that time, he became the founder of GenProject, a live electronic performance trio, soon to be included in Hip Production's booking roster, one of the major electronic music booking agency. Following the roster approval, GenProject performed at various clubs in Istanbul, such as Switch, Godet, Republic and Dulcinea. As an arranger, he produced many remixes and hits for many famous pop artists in Turkey. Gifted bass guitarist, driven by the passion for music he contributed to the recordings of around 50 hit albums released in the Turkish music industry. Currently he is producing, arranging and playing bass with various artists of Turkey and numerous projects all around Istanbul.

You know it's just about being progressive and forward thinking when it comes to EDM. Looking beyond what is seen into what things could come. Ion's sound is exactly like looking into a shattered mirror where you can see different angles. Finding the world; 'the system' too plain and ordinary to attach in, as the sole reality, she thinks about things noone can't see and uses her abstract imagination to dream up new worlds. She represents her inner thoughts and feelings with her tones, exhibiting colorful and varied sounds characterized by her order, progression, mentality and symmetry combined with her keen understanding of music and a style of sound shaping.

Her expressions usually focused on making people to feel "the moment", to dance and loose themselves in the catchy mental melodies comprising sharper sounds, progressive build ups and a flow to ride. Targeted to make people have their own inner journeys, Ion likes to create unique sound palettes for every different concept that she works. Aimed to reach the best possible build up and the most emotionally accelerated arrangement, her high frequency ranges usually works as a sunlight reflected to her dark lower range. Performances are strictly eclectic and groovy, constructed to impose powerful emotions to the audience. Stories hidden in her musical constructions, both at stage and in her records, lies in the inductive comprehension from the beginning to the end, and should be treated as a feature-movie script.

Catchy melodies and progressive build ups.. Somewhat acrid.. Sharp, not stuttering, but flowing.. Ranging anywhere between Minimal-Tech and Techno worlds. Denise Ion's music is definitely emotional, and designed to move people in both emotional and literal ways. She loves to work on themes like psychology, machineries, cosmology, biological fluxes, philosophy, science and technology. She likes to feel that she understands and probes deeply into a subject to get as good an insight as possible, open minded in to new ideas. 

On being innovative and experimental, which are quite relative subjects in EDM so as in art, she believes in an aesthetic balance between eccentric experimentalism and a solid dance groove. As musical trends change perpetually, she is excluding herself from being a certain sound trend setter. Instead, she has great appreciation and enough place inside her to embrace different visions. She finds it binding attaching to a certain specific kind of sound, with a mind with overflowing ideas. Ion loves to blend them in her own style and enjoys looking to the bigger picture as one of the many transformers in EDM. That's also the reason why she is called as the 'label mom'. 

BIOGRAPHY

Since she's the only child of a lyric soprano singer/songwriter mother with several EPs and LPs from late 70s and early 80s, she grew with music. Inherently caught in the frenzy of Michael Jackson that her mother made her listen through her pregnancy abdomen before Denise was born. In 90s her musical choices were names like Nine Inch Nails, Daft Punk, Faithless and Marilyn Manson.

The exact moment that she led by her passion for EDM, was the time when she listened to Josh Wink's epic "Don't Laugh" for the first time, and solidified with the renowned Radio 2019 of Istanbul, which has quite an impact on the birth of the EDM scene in 90s Turkey. Thankfully it was the Turkish legend in millenniums early stages, the Switch Club in Istanbul, which gave her the urge to dig deeper on the dance floor. After the very sad confinement of the club, she was determined to take a step further. 

From that moment in 2004, she has devoted herself to electronic dance music and she has appeared in numerous clubs, placed for festivals with names like Marilyn Manson, Groove Armada, Ellen Allien & Apparat, Kelis, Radioslave, Jamie Lidell, Booka Shade and so on to this day. Starting with the residency at Dogzstar in 2004, the doors opened and she played almost in every club and had several dj and producer projects ('Tuuce' 2003-2005, 'FA' duo project with Clone Kent 2005-2009 and ultimately Denise Ion from 2010 to present). To name the most noticeable ones; 'Auf' (Taylan Yilmaz) which played a leading role between 2005-2007 techno scene in Turkey with guests like Akufen, Christian Fischer, Dinky, M-in, Onur Ozer, Patrick Bateman, Savas Pascalidis, Seth Throxler, Tigerskin aka Dub Taylor and also the famous Indigo Club which was also legendary between 2005-2007 with such guests as Dave Clarke, Carl Craig, Richie Hawtin, Steve Bug, Gregor Tresher, Sven Vath, Alex Metric, Ambivalent, Ricardo Villalobos, Karotte, Alex Smoke, Onur Ozer, Italoboyz, Jennifer Cardini, André Galuzzi, Alex Flatner, Tobi Neumann, Monika Kruse and so on. For all others; Karakoy Liman, Lokal, Balans Tonique, Secret, Machine, MKZ Beach Party, Radar Live Festival 2007, Dirty and Smood would be the bests to name. After several club closings in 2009, she started playing at private parties made rarely at warehouses or cellars and organizing showcases for Redukt label.

Finding out that one can not be contented with only DJing when contaminated with EDM, as it was just the tip of the iceberg, studying Sound Production/Music Business was the second best thing that happened after her abrupt acquaintance with Clone Kent. By the beginning of her studies, a partnership has surfaced with Clone Kent and they started out a duo production and performance project named 'FA' in 2005. Until 2009, they made two albums and EPs, performed 10-channel mixes on stage and they grew mature in both music and stage. Denise that time, affected by Richie Hawtin's intelligent build ups and progressions, was also impressed by substantial composers like Jerry Goldsmith and Danny Elfman.

After the completion of the duo project, they have not only continued their partnership, but moved even further. They wanted to make their own contributions to the never-ending transformation of EDM, ending up with a desire to have and conduct a brand and in late 2009, they have founded Redukt label. Since that time, Ion is working together with a group of friends, deciding Redukt's inclinations on music, growing fanbase with solid releases and organizing label showcases to a multitude of enthusiasts. She has worked with (or still working with) labels like, Frucht (Berlin), Machine Box Music (Cabarete), Eye Records (Milan), Fourth Kind (Michigan), Volt9 (Utrecht), Hero In My Hood (Bayern).

name: Clone Kent
artist_bio:
“I want people to dance to my music with their eyes closed.  I want them to fly into the world of sophisticated senses, and besides hearing the music, I want them touch, smell, taste, and watch it.  It’s all about dense senses.  My tracks are generally about the world of darkness. Not evil, but a magical obscurity, like the night, that consists of hidden, epic stories that spread energy slowly and rhythmically.  I’m trying to put a spell on those who hear the music and transcend them to a place of calm euphoria.” – Clone Kent
Mystical, dark, infectious, provocative, and progressive, the music of artist Clone Kent provides an uncommon experience.  Upon hearing the first hypnotic beats of this artist’s Minimal Techno masterpieces, fans are transported to realm of mystery and secrets that allows them to release their inhibitions, dive in, and lose themselves in the music.  

Born in 1978 in Ankara, Turkey as Kaan Turkyilmaz, Clone Kent was genetically designed to make great music.  Growing up in a family of music-lovers, he studied piano, trumpet, and composing during his childhood, a time when he discovered his passion for music.  These early classical influences would later merge with a curiosity and affinity for his father’s Jupiter-8 and CR-78 electronic machines.  Blending those influences with others of pop and rock icons like Michael Jackson, Madonna, and Pink Floyd along with 80s electronic dance pioneers such as S-Express, M.A.R.R.S., and Technotronic gave life to the distinctive Clone Kent sounds audiences hear today.

In early 2004, desiring a greater inspiration for the music growing inside of him and richer club scene, he moved to Istanbul and launched “Fino Attack,” a production and performance project with friend Denise Ion.  Their first non-commercial album “Synthoxica,” which intermingled kitsch electro sounds of the 80s with analogue themes, was released in March 2006.  After a short time, in the fall of 2006, the second acid-electro album "Elektrolyted" was released from English fair play label BeatPick Music, and another release “i-Kontrol” was simultaneously released from Canadian label Bugeyed Records. During this time, the duo performed ten channel live electro and techno mixes in many of the hottest nightclubs in Turkey, which enhanced their exposure and made them wildly popular on the local club scene.  In 2008, Turkyilmaz began producing music with a more seasoned and sophisticated artistic perspective, and Clone Kent was born.

In 2009, Clone Kent and Ion began their own label, Redukt, which aims to test the creative boundaries of the techno arena with its wealth of fresh, new talent and their strikingly unique sounds.

With the goal of bringing the most exclusive, high quality Minimal Techno music to the world and becoming a positive force in the industry by merging musical intelligence, visual arts, intensive artistic collaboration, and quite simply, creating great dance music, Clone Kent continues to co-host Reduktiv Radio Show, produce remixes for other artists, and develop his own, innovative musical creations.

After the radio station was sold to a TV channel and changed its genre, DJ Tarkan continued playing his radio sets at FG till May 2007. His reputation in Turkey was spreading and the number of people appreciating his sound increasing with every event. The big break came in 2002 with the DJ of the Year award. 

Tarkan was sponsored to play his eclectic house sets, which he sharply forms depending on the time, the venue and the crowd, all around the country. His unique mixing style cemented his fan-base around the country, where he is frequently invited to play gigs in different cities. His creativity and talent was appreciated by the crowds and he was named number one DJ in Turkey for 3 consecutive years. 


Based on this success, DJ Tarkan decided to spend more time on productions, releasing tracks based on years of musical experience. His productions and remixes were included in the tracklists and charts of the world's well known dj's like Tiesto, Paul Oakenfold, Armin van Buuren, Sasha, Hernan Cattaneo, Nick Warren, Deep Dish, Sander Kleinenberg, Anthony Pappa, Dave Seaman, Danny Howells, Steve Lawler, Seb Fontaine, Lee Burridge, Desyn Masiello and many more.

While doing collaborative productions, Tarkan became close friends with V-SAG from Greece. Both went on tours together and the Turkish-Greek friendship resulted in the No Smoking Recordings label, which is intended to only release the highest standard of deep, tribal and progressive house music. DJ Tarkan and V-Sag have initiated a campaign for the understanding of the music "as is", giving people the opportunity to discover the true meaning of music in its purest form instead of "chemically enhanced fun".

This non-commercial album has a different point of view that forms a diversity from the other projects of FA.
 
In April 2006, Fino Attack’s radio show “ElectroStethoscope” has started on Turkey’s leading event organization / radio station Dinamo FM 103.8 (www.dinamo.fm). Fino Attack bound every saturday night to sundays with “ElectroStethoscope”. And, excellent mix links editorialized by Jon Spooner has chosen one of these performances as his pick at Blentwell (www.blentwell.com). Talented top dj’s like Misstress Barbara, Mark Romboy, Stephan Bodzin, Digitalism, Kiki, Monosurround etc., spinned their latest mixes for ElectroStethoscope as guest. “Circle of Cycle” Video Clip released on July 2006 and downloadable from Fino Attack’s web site. Their second album “Elektrolyted” happened as a result of a continious production concept which supports FA’s live performances. It presents a range between minimal electro and electro-techno with acidic and glitchy sounds. The album released out from the fairplay music label from England; BeatPick in fall, 2006 (www.beatpick.com). In November 2006, Fino Attack’s “iKontrol (The Grudge Attack Remix) released from the Canadian label; BugEyed Recordings (www.bugeyedrecorgins.com). At 2008 their two remixes for Clone Kent’s “Heavy Cat” & “Scodi” released from Jean Records (www.jeanrecords.co.uk).

Fino Attack’s live sound consists of multi channel djing of their own music and other artist’s tracks, drag & drop sessions, loop mixing and special fx control. They have performed at many jammy night clubs in several cities in Turkey.

name: Emir Hazir
artist_bio:
Emir Hazir

Techno Dj/Producer/Remix/EngineerThough Turkey may seem like an unlikely place for Techno, following in the tradition of fellow countrymen Len Faki and Butch; it is the home of a true hidden gem in Emir Hazir. Starting his career in music as a DJ at a popular turkish radio station, he discovered the world of production through a chance encounter with some analog gear at a friend's house in 2004. He immediately fell in love and the rest is history. Emir eventually moved onto software and spent the following years teaching himself how to produce by studying manuals, tutorials, and music as he gradually learned and refined his sound. His diligence paid off and Emir finally released his first EP, the formidable “Come Closer EP” on Feierkind Records in 2011. Applying it to a traditional society, however, was the real challenge. 

After completing high school, Uncuoglu started working at CD LAND, importing foreign LPs and the first CDs to Istanbul. Collecting a vast knowledge of the current dance music, he was approached with offers to DJ at private parties. In 1987, he began accepting the offers, and started his DJ’ing career. Soon his first residency, at Bodrum Hadigari, followed. 

Uncuoglu’s career took a professional turn when his success at Hadigari caught the attention of the owner of Pasha Istanbul and he was immediately recruited to the club. Before long, his name became simultaneous with Pasha as he transformed the club’s music scene to match that of the best in Europe.

His ever-increasing urge to become a professional DJ and producer, took Uncuoglu to what was then the heart of electronic music, London. During the day, he studied sound engineering and production at London’s Media Productions. At night, he conducted field research in London’s legendary clubs.        

While there, he met international producers including Marshall Jefferson (Chicago) and BAM BAM (Chicago) and worked as their engineers at various studios. It was not long before he was DJ’ing in exclusive parties and local clubs.

Upon his return to Istanbul in 1994, he embarked upon multiple projects. Consequently, he was recruited as the resident DJ at Club 2019, Istanbul’s legendary underground club. Simultaneously, Uncuoglu embarked on his most memorable project, the co-founding of Radio 2019, the first dance music radio station in Turkey. Thus, the first steps towards placing Istanbul on the club culture’s international map were taken. 

Uncuoglu has been the resident DJ at 7th House and Switch, the top two clubs in Istanbul, not to mention hosting  DJs  such as Sasha,John Digweed, Max Graham, Dave Seaman, Lemon8, Kasey Taylor,  Breeder , Phil Thomson .

Having attained national stardom and respect by both his fans and colleagues, Murat Uncuoglu has turned his attention to the international music scene.

name: Onur Özer
artist_bio:
Onur Ozer is a minimal techno DJ resident in Istanbul, Turkey.Ozer began his career in the late nineties when minimal and tech-house were making a resurgence in Istanbul.

In a city oppressed by both a stifling heat and a musical style equally as stagnant, Onur helped battle to change the old rules and break old habits, breathing fresh life into a dispirited club scene. Armed with his vinyl case, still dressed in his shabby student clothes, he entered the clubs to share his biggest passion, dancing without reason. 

Onur continued to fight the cause and helped found a number of new, vanguard venues, bringing new sounds and styles to Turkey’s capital.

In 2002 he began to export this warm Istanbul sound to different cities in Germany. Since then he has kept the crowds dancing in such venues as Robert Johnson, Harry Klein, Studio 672 and Kerosin.

2004 witnessed a turning point in his career and he became the resident DJ of the highly-rated party series Sweet Sense, welcoming many international acts.

In 2005 he began to take his already well-honed musical talents into the studio, releasing his debut EP ‘Freakdisco’ on Freude-Am-Tanzen in August. Another ‘Envy EP’ on Vakant the following month. Germany’s Groove Magazine rated him as one of their up and comers of the year.

2006 will see his next EP release on Vakant ‘Twilight’ out mid-March.

Messing up his dad's precious records in the family hi-fi was probably his first attempt with a turntable which was probably the first indication of his upcoming future. Music was in the background of his life, where he has addicted himself to basketball and played against current NBA players like Mehmet Okur of Utah Jazz and Hedo Turkoglu of Orlando Magic.

When he was 18, music became more than an interest after he bought his first set of 1210s. Infuenced primarily by Derrick May and his Chicago/Detroit style of discoish house and techno, he played his first gigs among house parties and amateur club parties. In 1998 he was accepted to the legendary Radio 2019, to host his 2 hour show 3 times weekly in the radio's Dance Department slot. His show at Radio 2019 went uninterrupted until March 2000 when the radio was sold and became an alternative rock radio. Until that time, he had proven his name alongside other leading dj's and was getting monthly and weekly residencies at clubs like Godet and Filter, which were considered as the best venues to dance to techno. Also getting gigs in nearly every club in Istanbul and playing in strong events like the 1st and 2nd A.d.A. Istanbul parties were the proof that his fans were not limited by only the technoheads in Turkey.

In 2002, Gokce was selected to be the first Turkish DJ at the infamous Red Bull Music Academy. Together with 29 other djs/producers, he went to Sao Paulo, Brazil, to meet and learn from electronic music icons like Robert Owens, Charlie May and DJ Marky. Also finding the opportunity to play at the local clubs and events in Sao Paulo, Gokce played his last techno set over there and came back to Turkey with the idea of changing and slowing down his music to a deeper level. Upon his return, he joined Radio FG, the leading electronic music station in Turkey. The change of his music caused the change of his name and he got the "Procombo" moniker which basically derived from a Chinese food menu. Playing a blend of music ranging from deep dubby tech house to deep techno, but mainly cruising at the progressive altitudes with a bit of breaks inbetween, Gokce had great support from FG to his new style and played together with some real important names like Hernan Cattaneo, Dave Seaman, Max Graham, John Creamer & Stephane K, James Holden and Rowan Blades in events like the massive Electronica Fest 2004/2005 and Global Gathering 2008/2009 and the Renessaince Masters series in Istanbul. .

Currently as Procombo, Gokce hosts his bi weekly radio shows in Radio FG every Wednesday (23:00-24:00) and which could be caught online through the radio's website www.futuregeneration.net. Also you can check out his website www.procombo.net for more....

Peaceful Mind is a dedicated progressive lover, but isn’t imprisoned by a single genre, saying “What makes progressive work so well is that it doesn’t stick to one style, and can incorporate electro, minimal, whatever it likes.” Although has clearly reached a celebrity status, it¹s his generous personality, his love for his peers and of course his completely candid humour that has enabled him to maintain such a likeable high profile in the often-fickle world of club culture.Born in Izmir, Turkey to a musical family, Peaceful Mind indulged his passion for music from a young age. Peaceful Mind is a dedicated progressive lover, but isn’t imprisoned by a single genre, saying “What makes progressive work so well is that it doesn’t stick to one style, and can incorporate electro, minimal, whatever it likes.” Although has clearly reached a celebrity status, it¹s his generous personality, his love for his peers and of course his completely candid humour that has enabled him to maintain such a likeable high profile in the often-fickle world of club culture.

For Peaceful Mind, music is his first love, and what gives him a buzz is being able to share his music with others. From his presence at those all too talked about after hour parties where his special sets are heard, to his signature always present child like antics that leave people wondering if he has modelled his life all lined with the backdrop of his own productions, Peaceful Mind leaves trails of memories, melodies and stories wherever he goes. name: Skull & Bones
artist_bio:
Turkey (Turk & American) based, Old Indie-Dubstep, Chiptune music duo. First Dubstep & Chiptune music group in Turkey. Skull & Bones, Skull House; Jasty Minas & Gorkem Deniz as established in July 2011.(!) This biography was written with Turkish.

Türkiye'de henüz yeni yeni Dubstep / Indie türleri yükselmeye başlamışken; Haziran 2011 tarihinde, Görkem Deniz Şahin (5 Subat 1994) ve Jasty Minas (3 Ocak 1993) birlikte "Skull & Bones" grubunu kurmuş, Antalya'da "Skull House" plak şirketi adı altında bu türde parçalar yayınlamaya başlamıştır. Türk ve Amerikan olan bu ikili, dönemin popüler parçalarına yaptıkları remikslerle türün dinleyicileri tarafından beğeni kazanmıştır.
Grubun ilk 2 ayı yarım bırakılan, tasarlanıp hayata geçirilemeyen bir çok proje ve taslak sebebiyle sessiz geçmiştir. Ilk remiks olarak, Ağustos 2011'de grup "Party Rock & ET Remixes" adını verdikleri promo 2 remiks yayınlamıştır. Ilk orijinal parça olarak, aynı ay içerisinde grup "Foster's Zombie House" adında 2 parçalık bir EP yayınlamıştır. Eylül 2011'de grup, Jasty Minas'ın eğitimi dolayısıyla Los Angeles'a dönmesinden itibaren 7 ay yeni bir proje yayınlamamıştır.

2012 yılbaşında Jasty Minas, Türkiye'ye dönmüş ve Skull & Bones gelecek bir ay için yeni projeler üretmeye başlamıştır. Şubat 2012'de grup Daft Punk'ın "Harder, Better, Faster, Stronger" adındaki parçasının, 2 farklı versionunu yayınlamıştır. Bonus olarak Kanye West'in Stronger parçasını da bu promo arasına eklenmiştir. Aynı ay içerisinde, Görkem Deniz Şahin'in doğum günü sebebiyle grup özel bir parti düzenlemiştir. Mart 2012'de grup Türkiye'de 7 şehirde etkinliklere katılacaklarını, turne yapacaklarını duyurmuştur. Aynı ay içerisinde grup, "Dark Energy" adında bir Single yayınlamıştır ve Burn Studios Mix-Off Sessions 2012 yarışmasına katılmış, yarı finale yükselmiştir. Mayıs 2012'de grubun turnesi sona ermiş ve "4 Revolution" adında 4'lük remiks promo yayınlamıştır. Haziran 2012'de grup "Blondown" adında bir Single yayınlamıştır. Aynı ay içerisinde grup "Analog Eurasia	" adında haftalık bir radyo yayını yapmayı planlamış fakat bu fikir 5. bölümden sonra iptal edilmiştir.  Temmuz 2012'de grup "Avrupa Star DJ'ini Arıyor" yarışmasına katılmış ve yarışma için "First Year Anniversary Mix" adında bir set yayınlamıştır. Yarışma daha sonra iptal olmuş, grup aynı ay içerisinde 11 şehirde ve 2 ülkede etkinliklere katılacaklarını, turneye hazırlandıklarını açıklamıştır. Aynı ay içerisinde grup Daft Punk'ın "Derezzed" parçasına remiks yapmıştır. Kasım 2012'de turneler sona erdi ve bu tarihde ikili arasında tartışma yaşandı, grup bahaneler sebebiyle çalışmayı durdurduklarını açıkladı.

2013 yılbaşında Görkem Deniz Şahin, grubun tekrar bir araya geldiğini açıkladı. Ayrıca Ikili tarzlarını da değiştireceklerini, henüz bunun üzerinde çalıştıklarını, herhangi bir sonuca ulaşamadıklarını da belirtti. Deneysel bir çalışma olarak grup, Ocak 2013'de "The Oracle Lys" adında bir set yayınladı. Bu deneyimden mutlu olmayan ikili Şubat 2013'de yeni tarzlarının "Chiptune" olacağını açıkladı. Grup, Indie / Dubstep dönemine ait tüm kayıtları kaldırdı ve tamamiyle "Chiptune" türüne yöneldi. Değişim ile birlikte grubun ilk remiksi Daft Punk'ın "Around The World" parçasına oldu. Aynı ay içerisinde grup; James Horner'ın Braveheart filminin ana teması başta olmak üzere; "A Gift of A Thistle", "Wallace Courts Murron", "The Secret Wedding", "Murron's Burial", "Sons of Scotland", "For The Love of A Princess", "Freedom, The Execution Bannockburn" parçalarına, Daft Punk'ın "Da Funk" ve Deadmau5'un "Strobe" parçasına remiks yaptı. Mart 2013'de grup Daft Punk'ın remikslerinin bulunduğu bir "Remixes, Compilation Album" yayınlayacaklarını duyurdu; "The World Is Daft". Aynı ay içerisinde grup, Daft Punk'ın "Aerodynamic" ve "Digital Love" parçalarına, Lorne Balfe'nin Assasin's Creed III oyunu için yaptığı "Assasin's Creed III Main Theme" parçasına remiks yaptı. Nisan 2013'de grup Ke$ha'nın "Your Love Is My Drug" ve Daft Punk'ın "Harder, Better Faster Stronger" parçalarına 2 versiyon halinde (Extended, Instrumental) remiks, Jeremy Soule'un The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim adlı oyun için yaptığı "The Dragonborn Comes" parçasına mini-mix yapmıştır. Mayıs 2013'de yaz döneminin ortasına kadar yeni bir parça yayınlamayacaklarını belirten grup turne hazırlığına başlamıştır. name: Subsky
artist_bio:
Goktug Citci was born in a beautiful city called Istanbul, in 1979.He came across with electronic music in the beginning of 90s, and started listening to everything he could find.

The archive he had been accumulating over the years was neither fitting his house, nor his soul anymore. What gave him a buzz is being able to share his music with others, so with the thought of -Music is best when shared-, he started a radio show at the now defunct: Radio Cool, where he also started tampering with music production. This was the year 1997.

Fast-forward to 2001, and the first product of his newly established home studio was “Cervus – Faraway” on XTC Records. His second release on Sadie Records, “Four Days” was featured in Paul Van Dyk’s “Politics of Dancing” compilation; which also marks the birth of Subsky.

Starting in 2003, he was releasing his hazy, melancholic, melodic and intelligent dance music infused with groovy eclectic themes back to back on respected labels. “Strawberry Fields”, which appears on Nick Warren’s GU24 Reykjavik, is one of those that makes you go: Sounds like Subsky!

2004 witnessed the launch of Red Flag Collective, the label that he formed with Yunus Guvenen, Baris Turker and Muzo B. “Let it Flow” was the second release on RFC and it enjoyed the top spot of the Balance Chart.

His booty of Miss Kittin’s “Professional Distortion” was a huge hit with Sasha and had a dwell on everyone else’s mind who partied that summer.

In addition to his production career, he’s been djing in Turkey and around the globe for the past 10 years. He was crowned the No. 1 dj in Turkey in 2005. With a career that is punctuated by landmark achievements, he tries to reflect his own sound to his dj sets and he is known as a ‘satisfaction guaranteed’ dj by partygoers and promoters in Turkey.

He is also part of the Dinamo 103.8 FM crew in Istanbul, working as a Music Director and Production Manager.

Check out Subsky’s show, every Wed. 10 pm till 11 pm (gmt+2) on Istanbul’s urban-electronic radio station "Dinamo 103.8" – http://www.dinamo.fm

name: Ugur Project
artist_bio:
booking@audiolove.deUğur Altıntaş aka Ugur Project was born in 1982, in İstanbul Turkey. He started his music career when he was only 16 years old. Back then he was already a part of the first and only dance music radio station “Radio 2019”.  While working and undergoing a hard training of Production and Radio Shows he met with trance genre which amazed him at the first sight.

After a while Uğur set sailed for another adventure on Turkish nationwide radio and television news channel “NTV”.  Working in production jobs as a technical crew he got enough experience to form a New Radio channel “Radyo Eksen” with his fellow friends.

Between 2001 and 2004 he started to produce his own music and worked with the best dance music radios such as “Cool” and “Radio Quasar” while hosting a radio show that consists of techno sets. 

He worked hard on the stage just as in the studio.  Between 2001 and 2010 he performed in the highly respected clubs such as Filter, JukeBox, Switch, Republic, Cantina, Filter and Spoon. It goes the same with the festivals. While showing his skills at Parkorman, Maslak Venue and Solar Beach, he shared the stage with the big guns like; Kraftwerk, Faithless, Chemical Brothers and Moby. Especially with his performances in İstanbul and Radio&Tv shows he both hosted and attended he got the chance to made the crowds hear his music.

Even with his busy schedule between 2010 and 2013 he managed to host a radio show called “HardGroove” at Dinamo FM 103.8.
Musically speaking innovation is his motto. With the projects he put through he managed to bring a new meaning to night life. He organized parties at the biggest night clubs back then. Biggest example to that is “Technodays”. It was the first performance ever in Turkey with 9 records players, 3 mixers and 3 DJ’s playing at the same time. When he was only 23 years old he already reached his 500th performance mark. At that night he decided to tribute his DJ’ing career with a production career.

His first project was his track “Turn Around” in the Turkey’s first electronic music compilation album “Future Sound Of Istanbul House Workz” released by EMI and Prosound. This track helped Uğur to demonstrate his production skills and also helped foreign Recording Labels to discover the artist. Just after signing a contract with FHD Records, at 5 May 2008 he released “Turbulence EP” with FHD Records a highly respected company based on UK. Only 3 months later “Zeplin Ep” was released. While improving his production skills and spending most of his free time to music, he started working with more and more Recording Labels. And without a surprise he got a lot of good feedbacks along the way.

After the digital releases Uğur was quite excited about having his first record released by the German Record Label “Thokadee”. After the first week of release his “Dope Ep” was already reached number 4 at the list. One of the special things about this Record was its colour. It was white and the B side of the record has the symbol of moon and the star symbolizing Turkish flag.  Coming right after one another his other records share the same success with his first records. His works got remixed by Spencer K, Alex Q, Francesco Bonora, Cess, Alex Costa, Ronan Portela, Oscar Barila, Jay Kurmis, Israel VichSergio Parrado Mario Aureo, IPagan and helped his music to reach the masses. After all the hard work he started to cooperate with internationally famous names. Always keeping connection with Turkey, he started to work with two successful producer named Sarp Yılmaz and Sinan Kaya.  With a collaboration like that their remixes and EP’s reached far beyond Turkey’s borders. 
Another big project was with Angelo Ferreri. With the help of famous Back and Forth Records owned by Cosmic Cowboys they released Sad Moment EP. It was in over 100 DJ charts. In 2013 his “Diren/Gezi” record was published by Ostwind Records. After that record published he became the Turkey’s number 1 for being in almost every DJ chart in Europe.

Spending his free time mostly in the Studio Uğur was in over 40 Solo, 50 Compilation albums and remixed over 30 artists. Without productivity concerns he is known as hardest working DJ/Producer.

Nowadays he is working on a project to form Audiolove Recordings with his old friend German Producer DJ Ali Özoğlu aka Cess. Within all the fuss he is performing at clubs every month.

Born in Seattle, Washington, raised in Istanbul, Turkey; Murad L began his musical journey DJ-ing in Tampa Florida’s thriving underground house scene. His DJ sets range from Deep, Tech, Disco, Jazz and Funk; and over the years he has performed for the House community across mainland Europe and the US. After moving back to Miami, Murad became one of the most versatile producers in the scene; claiming respect from DJs all over the country and rest of the world. He has had productions with Cem sessions for labels such as, Casa Del Soul, Greenhouse, Odds & Ends, Guess and compilation albums for clubs such as Cielo NY , La Playa Ibiza and annual Pacha complations under the guise of “The Craftsmen“. His Tracks charted by one of the most important names in the business such as Pete Tong, Ben Watt..In 2007 Murad L. moved to Istanbul, where he started his weekly radio show Yakuza Beats at Dinamo 103.8 fm. In 2009 he started StarSeed Recordings to deliver deep techy soulful house music.

Being a good listener from an early age, Tolga finally decided to make music at 17 and took up guitar and music harmony lessons. This led him to discover more sophisticated music genres like Jazz and Blues. He learned to play trumpet which saw him join a Blues band called "Harlot Money" during his college years.

Continuously searching for innovation, he discovered electronic music and started to collect vinyls and began DJing at the clubs in Ankara eventualy gaining residency at The Club 20 a year later. He now travels extensively playing in Berlin, Warsaw, Krakow, Wroclaw, Johannesburg, Cape Town and most recently Chengdu. He played at the prestigious 10th Era New Horizons International Film Festival in Poland in 2010. He always expresses his devotion to the techno scene in his dj sets. As a producer, he began to make his way in the architecture of creative and sophisticated minimalism. 

Already released on labels like Lebensfreude Records, Archipel Musique, Resopal Schallware,, Android Muziq, Labrynth, Living Records, Kalimari Musique Psycle Records, but there is much more to come. His vinyl release “Lovin” was charted by Thomas Schumacher, Technasia and played by Loco Dice, Chloe, Margaret Dygas, Brothers Vibe, Hugo, Tini, Jens Bond, Someone Else, etc., whereas his "Blues EP" vinyl had been reviewed by famous De:Bug Magazine. 

His own techno imprint VENT has had releases played by Shifted most recently and features some new and established talent including Arbiter, Miss Sunshine, DJ Skirt,Zadig. He defines his interest in music as "passion”.
